## Production Execution Checklist

### Pre-Flight (Before ANY SQL)

- [ ] **Read this entire document**
- [ ] Open Supabase SQL Editor
- [ ] Have a second browser tab with `profiles` table visible
- [ ] Note current `profiles` count: `SELECT count(*) FROM profiles WHERE deleted_at IS NULL;`
- [ ] Note current `permissions` count: `SELECT count(*) FROM permissions;`
- [ ] Confirm you are logged in as L3 admin

### Execution Order

| Step | Script | Reversible? | Verify Before Next |
|------|--------|:-----------:|---------------------|
| 1 | `001_create_user_permissions.sql` | ✅ `DROP TABLE` | Check tables exist in Supabase table editor |
| 2 | `002_normalize_permissions_table.sql` | ✅ `original_module` column has backups | `SELECT DISTINCT module FROM permissions;` — no `stock_movements` etc. |
| 3 | `003_create_staging_table.sql` | ✅ `DROP TABLE` | Staging table visible in editor |
| 4 | **Frontend: Push localStorage data** | N/A | See frontend migration code below |
| 5 | `004_merge_staging_to_user_permissions.sql` | ✅ Staging has status tracking | `SELECT count(*) FROM user_permissions;` |
| 6 | `005_effective_permissions_function.sql` | ✅ `DROP FUNCTION` | Run validation query #5 |
| 7 | `006_feature_flag.sql` | ✅ `advance_permission_rollout('localStorage')` | Flag shows `'localStorage'` |
| 8 | `007_security_hardening.sql` | ✅ `DROP POLICY` | Test: L1 user can read own perms |
| 9 | `008_validation_queries.sql` | N/A | All checks pass |
| 10 | **Frontend: Deploy new permissionService** | ✅ Feature flag controls source | Test app behavior |
| 11 | Set flag: `db_with_fallback` | ✅ Revert to `localStorage` | Monitor for 1-3 days |
| 12 | Set flag: `db_only` | ✅ Revert to `db_with_fallback` | Monitor for 1 week |
| 13 | **Frontend: Remove localStorage code** | ⚠️ Code change (git revert) | Final validation |
| 14 | Set flag: `cleanup_done` | ✅ | Drop staging table |

### Failure Recovery Plan

```
IF migration fails at Step 1-3:
  → DROP new tables. Zero impact on existing system.

IF migration fails at Step 4-5:
  → Staging table has FAILED status. Fix and re-run.
  → user_permissions can be TRUNCATEd safely.

IF migration fails at Step 6-8:
  → DROP new functions/policies.
  → System falls back to localStorage (still works).

IF migration fails at Step 10-12:
  → Run: SELECT advance_permission_rollout('localStorage');
  → Instantly reverts. Zero downtime.

IF everything fails:
  → Run ROLLBACK LEVEL 3 script.
  → System returns to exact pre-migration state.
  → User permissions archive preserved in user_permissions_archive table.
```

